OL,4,Clifeboat crew who rescued them off
OL,5,CSussex coast
OL,7,FThe RNLI and Paddle UK (the national
OL,8,Fgoverning body for paddlesports) are
OL,9,Furging people to always wear a
OL,10,Fbuoyancy aid, tell someone where
OL,11,Fyou're going, carry a mobile phone,
OL,12,Fcheck the weather, and know your
OL,13,Flimits.
OL,15,FRNLI National Water Safety Partner,
OL,16,FSam Hughes, said: 'We always want
OL,17,Fpeople to enjoyJour coastline but we
OL,18,Fare urging everyone to think carefully
OL,19,Fbefore heading out.
